159.question: What is typical GAN architecture for each text-to-image synhesis group?
159.response:
{'Answer': 'The typical Generative Adversarial Network (GAN) architectures for text-to-image synthesis can be categorized by their focus on improving different aspects of the generated images:

1. Semantic Enhancement GANs: These models aim to improve the alignment between the text description and the semantic content of the generated images. Examples include GAN-INT-CLS and DCGAN which utilize text descriptions to refine image details during generation.

2. Resolution Enhancement GANs: These GAN architectures work on producing higher resolution images that remain consistent with the text input. StackGAN and StackGAN++ are notable examples that use a multi-stage generation
159.answer:
Semantic Enhancement GANs: DC-GANs, MC-GAN
Resolution Enhancement GANs: StackGANs, AttnGAN, HDGAN
Diversity Enhancement GANs: AC-GAN, TAC-GAN etc.
Motion Enhancement GAGs: T2S, T2V, StoryGAN
